name: New Hampshire Corned Beef Dip
author: McCormick Spice
summary: The tradition of the New England boiled dinner – a one-pot dish featuring corned beef, cabbage, carrots and potatoes – lives on! Recreate that irresistible taste with a dip featuring simple but flavorful ingredients. Mix cream cheese and Swiss cheese with plain Greek yogurt and flavor with McCormick® Guacamole Seasoning Mix. Blend with corned beef and chill until game time. Dip with carrot sticks, bread or assorted crackers.
ingredients: 4 ounces cooked corned beef, shredded or finely chopped
1 (1 ounce) package McCormick® Guacamole Seasoning Mix
directions: Mix all ingredients, except parsley flakes, in a large bowl until well blended
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve
